{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|辡|言|c1=p|c2=s|t2=say|ls=psc}}. However, the phonetic component (which is the reduplication of the Kangxi radical of the knife to mark prisoners) perhaps symbolizes two prisoners accusing each other, hence "debating in an aggressive manner". {{attention|zh|the Japanese page for 辡 rejects 辡 representing knives as an incorrect analysis by Shuowen}}

